The paper deals with designing fixed-parameter algorithms for cut problems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of algorithms and computational complexity. The use of randomized contractions is a technique that is relevant to both these sub-fields, and hence cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are relevant to cs.CG and cs.GT. Finally, the paper involves analysis of algorithms and running time analysis, which are relevant to cs.LG.
